    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-11-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-11-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="652"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d652">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Storer</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-11-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 21, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram of the 17th instant concerning delivery of Spanish prisoners by
                    Filipinos had due consideration. Reports from general commanding show that real
                    obstacle to surrender lies in the insistence of Filipinos that Spain recognize
                    insurgent government as condition for return of prisoners. Surrender to vessel
                    flying Spanish flag is inadmissible, being tacit recognition. Delivery of
                    prisoners to vessel flying Geneva Red Cross flag would be entirely
                    unobjectionable, and General Otis will be instructed to facilitate such delivery
                    by every means in his power. It is, however, apprehended that the insurgents
                    will refuse this.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
